Package org.opengis.metadata

The metadata root entity.

Metadata object are described in the OpenGIS® Metadata (Topic 11) specification. The following table shows the class hierarchy, together with a partial view of aggregation hierarchy:

Package overview
Class hierarchy Aggregation hierarchy 
 ISO 19115 object
  ├─ Metadata
  ├─ MetadataScope
  ├─ PortrayalCatalogueReference
  ├─ ApplicationSchemaInformation
  ├─ MetadataExtensionInformation
  ├─ ExtendedElementInformation
  └─ Identifier
 CodeList
  ├─ Datatype
  └─ Obligation
 
 Metadata
  ├─ MetadataScope
  ├─ PortrayalCatalogueReference
  ├─ ApplicationSchemaInformation
  ├─ MetadataExtensionInformation
  │   └─ ExtendedElementInformation
  │       ├─ Datatype «code list»
  │       └─ Obligation «code list»
  └─ Identifier
Since:
2.0
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ApplicationSchemaInformation
    Defines and exposes the structure of a resource (model and/or data dictionary).
    ExtendedElementInformation
    New metadata element, not found in ISO 19115, which is required to describe geographic data.
    FeatureTypeList Deprecated.
    Not anymore in ISO 19115.
    Identifier
    Value uniquely identifying an object within a namespace.
    Metadata
    Root entity which defines metadata about a resource or resources.
    MetadataExtensionInformation
    Information describing metadata extensions.
    MetadataScope
    Class of information to which the referencing entity applies.
    PortrayalCatalogueReference
    Information identifying the portrayal catalogue used.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Datatype
    Datatype of element or entity.
    Obligation
    Obligation of the element or entity.
